program?\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T03:01:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36444498","id":36444498,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ0NDk4","updated_at":"2014-03-02T03:01:42.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36444498","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley, thanks for working with me on this.\n\nI think I've found my issue: If I take the OrbitControls sample file (http:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/#misc_controls_orbit) and add a different cameraTarget in the line after setting the position, the OrbitControls will neglect the Camera Target when the Event Listener initiates the render() function.  If I add camera.Lookat(CameraTarget) to the render function, the view remains, but the Orbit Controls get whacky.\n\nI'm new to Three, so I may be missing something.  Is there a proper approach to customizing the cameraTarget when using OrbitControls?\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T04:31:24.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36445830","id":36445830,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ1ODMw","updated_at":"2014-03-02T04:31:24.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36445830","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6820526?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ekatzenstein","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4MjA1MjY=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ekatzenstein","type":"User","id":6820526,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"I'm noticing this line in OrbitControls.js:\n\n```\n\/\/ \"target\" sets the location of focus, where the control orbits around\n\/\/ and where it pans with respect to.\nthis.target = new THREE.Vector3();\n```\n\nIs there a way to adjust this to your camera target as defined in the main script?  I tried adding a variable but it was no longer rendering.\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T04:41:45.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36445960","id":36445960,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ1OTYw","updated_at":"2014-03-02T04:41:45.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36445960","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6820526?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ekatzenstein","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4MjA1MjY=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ekatzenstein","type":"User","id":6820526,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@ekatzenstein \n\nAs stated in the [guidelines](https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/master\/CONTRIBUTING.md), help requests should be directed to [stackoverflow](http:\/\/stackoverflow.com\/questions\/tagged\/three.js). This board is for bugs and feature requests.\n\nIf you need help, I will be glad to help you with three.js questions on SO, but I can't help you debug your code.\n\nIs it true that modifying the camera's `up` vector is no longer an issue for you?\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T04:47:15.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36446032","id":36446032,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ2MDMy","updated_at":"2014-03-02T04:47:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36446032","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Sorry for the lack of etiquette, I'm somewhere in between calling this an issue and needing support.  To close it out, I _think_ I figured out the issue with camera targets:\n\nAs the OrbitControls.js is setup, it automatically orbits around a camera target of (0,0,0):\n\nLine 34:\n\n```\n\/\/ \"target\" sets the location of focus, where the control orbits around\n\/\/ and where it pans with respect to.\nthis.target = new THREE.Vector3();\n\n\/\/ center is old, deprecated; use \"target\" instead\nthis.center = this.target;\n```\n\nNow, to add a cameraTarget from your script, add a variable to the function:\n\nLine 24:\n        THREE.OrbitControls = function ( object, domElement) {\n\nchange this to: \n        THREE.OrbitControls = function ( object, domElement, camTar) {\n\nand update line 34 to:\n\n```\n\/\/ \"target\" sets the location of focus, where the control orbits around\n\/\/ and where it pans with respect to.\nthis.target = camTar;\n\/\/ this.camera.Lookat=new THREE.Vector3( 0, 500,100);\n\/\/ center is old, deprecated; use \"target\" instead\nthis.center = camTar;\n```\n\nAnd when calling the function in your main file:\n\ninstead of:\n        controls = new THREE.OrbitControls( camera);\ngo with\n        controls = new THREE.OrbitControls( camera,document,cameraTarget );\n\nMay be worthwhile to update OrbitControls.js for this functionality, but I don't want to step on any toes as I'm new to GitHub. \n\nIn this current case, the camera.up vector is not an issue.  It was instead a camera target issue.  Thanks for your help and please let me know what you think about updating Orbit Controls to have a custom camera target.\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T04:58:20.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36446190","id":36446190,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ2MTkw","updated_at":"2014-03-02T05:00:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36446190","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6820526?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/ekatzenstein","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4MjA1MjY=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"ekatzenstein","type":"User","id":6820526,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/ekatzenstein\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I believe all you need to do is this:\n\n```\ncontrols = new THREE.OrbitControls( camera, renderer.domElement );\ncontrols.target.copy( vector );\n```\n","created_at":"2014-03-02T05:13:01.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-36446414","id":36446414,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM2NDQ2NDE0","updated_at":"2014-03-02T05:13:01.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/36446414","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"auth