":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":13,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley\r\nThank you for the comment!\r\n\r\nWe can initialize like this.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\ncontrols = new THREE.OrbitControls( camera, renderer.domElement );\r\ncontrols.target.copy( vector );   \/\/ initial position\r\ncontrols.target0.copy( vector );  \/\/ reset position\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt's OK, but I think it would be better if the `target0` was hidden from users.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nfunction setTarget( vector ) {\r\n  scope.target.copy( vector );\r\n  scope.target0.copy( vector );\r\n}\r\n```\r\n","created_at":"2017-02-19T16:58:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-280931889","id":280931889,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4MDkzMTg4OQ==","updated_at":"2017-02-19T16:58:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/280931889","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11028?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/koseki","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMDI4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"koseki","type":"User","id":11028,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/orgs"}},{"index":14,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@koseki The problem is that not all users may want the reset target to be updated whenever the target is set.\r\n\r\nThis is the reason `OrbitControls` is in the examples -- because users want to change its behavior.\r\n","created_at":"2017-02-19T18:34:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-280938306","id":280938306,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4MDkzODMwNg==","updated_at":"2017-02-19T18:34:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/280938306","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":15,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley \r\n\r\nThe `reset()` method means `reset to the initial state`, so I feel it is natural to remember the `target` value (not `target0`).\r\nIf we have to set the position manually, It's not `reset` but just `set`, I think.\r\n\r\n> not all users may want the reset target to be updated whenever the target is set.\r\n\r\nWe can call `setTarget()` again, because we want to `reset()` somewhere else, other than the current target position.\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontrols.setTarget(vector);\r\ncontrols.reset();\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnyway, it's OK if this is intended design.\r\nThank you for reading my idea!\r\n","created_at":"2017-02-20T00:41:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513#issuecomment-280963506","id":280963506,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/4513","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI4MDk2MzUwNg==","updated_at":"2017-02-20T04:33:36.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/280963506","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/11028?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/koseki","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMDI4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/koseki\/repos","received_events_u